						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">That's the problem. For each Super NES Mouse accessory I buy and destroy, a copy of Mario Paint becomes useless. It'd be like using Mario Paint as a donor cart for my own development, and the whole idea of buying a PowerPak was to get away from donor carts. That's why I wanted to go the extension cord route, so that I can still use my Mario Paint Game Pak in my Super NES.</div>
<br />
<br />I thought everyone cut up cheap $3 SNES and NES extension cables for this? I got fancy on mine because I got a good price on DIN-5 inline connectors and cut them in half, put the DIN-5 in-between so I can swap the SNES for the NES ends and mix NES and SNES accessories on either system. Obviously software support is necessary for it to work, but the hardware appears moderately compatible.</div>

